Package com.genesyslab.platform.contacts.protocol.contactserver.requests

Class RequestContactListGet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.genesyslab.platform.commons.protocol.DataObject
      • com.genesyslab.platform.commons.protocol.Message
        • com.genesyslab.platform.contacts.protocol.contactserver.AbstractMessage
          • com.genesyslab.platform.contacts.protocol.contactserver.requests.RequestContactListGet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EndpointSupport, ProtocolDescriptionSupport, Referenceable, DataSupport, com.genesyslab.platform.commons.protocol.runtime.UpdatableProtocolId, ContactServerMessage, Printable, RequestorInfoSupport
    public final class RequestContactListGet
extends AbstractMessage
    This request is intended for building a ScrollableList object based on provided constraints. Depending on the Restricted parameter, lookup filter is applied in Contact table or in ContactAttribute table. Depending on database indexes, the type of Operator used, the size of the tables, and many other parameters, it can be more interesting (in terms of performance) to set Restricted to TRUE or to FALSE. There is no general rule and this really depends on the filter used, and on the database used. Because the Contact table contains only a subset of Contact Attribute values (they are called sortable Contact Attributes), it is not possible to use any Contact Attribute in a filter when Restricted is set to TRUE. Note also that the data returned by the lookup request comes from the Contact table only. In the same way, the ordering of the Contacts returned is done using Contact data only.

    Required parameters:
    Name Description
    setTenantId(java.lang.Integer) The unique tenant ID.

    Related Events:
    Name Description
    EventContactListGet This event indicates that the RequestContactListGet was successful, and contains a list of contacts matching the criteria specified in that request. Note that data returned in EventContactListGet comes from the Contact table only. In the same way, the ordering of the Contacts returned is done using Contact data only.
    EventError Indicates that the request encountered an error.
